A Tony Award-winning musical "Spring Awakening" explores the stage in
adolescence when the discovery of sexuality brings sudden changes. Based on a
19th century German play, the musical is set to a rock and roll score and
examines the tortured inner lives of a group of adolescents. VOA's Zhang Zheng
and Joseph Mok have this report from Broadway, narrated by Elaine Lu. 
 
 
 
 

